Coal-Train Crash in Russian Urals Region Kills 2, Interfax Says

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-08-11T16:49:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/coal-train-crash-in-russian-urals-region-kills-2-interfax-says.html
Two people were killed after a 67-
car coal train collided with another train and derailed in
 Russia ’s Urals region, Interfax said, citing the country’s
Emergency Ministry.  Forty-four trains were stopped because of the accident,
which happened at 6 p.m. Moscow time, the newswire reported.  To contact the reporters on this story: Yuliya Fedorinova in
Moscow at   yfedorinova@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  